        <main class="policy-container">
            <section class="section-heading">
                <h1>Travel Policies</h1>
                <p>Effective Date: May 19, 2025</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>1. Booking Requirements</h2>
                <p>Passengers must ensure all information provided at the time of booking is accurate. Any discrepancies may result in denied boarding or additional fees.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>2. Identification and Documentation</h2>
                <p>All travelers are required to carry valid government-issued photo identification. International travelers must possess valid passports and any applicable visas.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>3. Baggage Policy</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Carry-on baggage must not exceed size and weight limits specified on our website.</li>
                    <li>Checked baggage allowances vary by fare class and route. Excess baggage may incur fees.</li>
                    <li>Prohibited items include weapons, flammable substances, and certain electronics.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>4. Check-In and Boarding</h2>
                <p>Passengers must check in at least 2 hours before departure for domestic flights and 3 hours for international flights. Boarding gates close 20 minutes before departure.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>5. Flight Changes and Cancellations</h2>
                <p>Flight changes are subject to availability and may incur fees. Cancellations are handled per the fare rules selected during booking.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>6. Travel Disruptions</h2>
                <p>In case of delays, cancellations, or other disruptions, FlyDreamAir will offer rebooking options or refunds in line with our service terms and local regulations.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>7. Passenger Conduct</h2>
                <p>FlyDreamAir expects all passengers to conduct themselves respectfully. Unruly behavior may result in removal from the aircraft or a ban from future flights.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="policy-section">
                <h2>8. Contact and Assistance</h2>
                <p>For questions or special assistance, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@flydreamair.com">support@flydreamair.com</a>.</p>
            </section>
        </main>

